PSV frontman Memphis Depay has been tipped to  match Arjen Robben and even touted as a better player than Cristiano Ronaldo at the same age.

With 16 Eredivisie strikes to his name, the 21-year-old winger has stormed to the top of the goalscoring charts this season and even found the net for Holland at the World Cup in Brazil last summer.

Wanted by Manchester United and Tottenham, Depay may well depart the Philips Stadion at the end of the season after PSV admitted it may be difficult to keep him at the club. 

