Top of the scoring charts 

Depay's strike during Saturday's 3-0 win away at Go Ahead Eagles was his 16th of the season and took him to the top of the Eredivisie goalscoring charts - one  ahead of PSV team-mate Luuk De Jong. An impressive feat for a player who is not an all-out attacker.

The No 7 has enjoyed a steady flow of goals during the last two seasons and has found the net 19 times in all competitions this term.

Scoring four braces, Depay's goals from out wide have helped fire PSV eleven points clear at the top of the Eredivisie table and will have certainly caught the eye of Europe's biggest clubs.

